Extracted Variables:
- Let x be the number of bus trips
- Let y be the number of car trips

Extracted Constraints:
- x \leq 10 (maximum number of bus trips)
- x + y \geq 0.6 * (x + y) (at least 60% of the trips must be by car)
- 100x + 40y \geq 1200 (total number of chicken to transport)

Extracted Objective:
- Minimize 2x + 1.5y (total time needed to transport the chicken)
